# Add container cleanup to AgentServer terminate

Ensure containers are properly cleaned up when agent stops.

## Requirements

- Stop and remove container on AgentServer terminate
- Handle both graceful and crash shutdowns
- Cleanup volumes if configured
- Update ContainerRegistry

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] AgentServer `terminate/2` calls `ContainerSupervisor.stop_container/1`
- [ ] Container stopped with grace period before kill
- [ ] Container removed from Docker after stop
- [ ] ContainerRegistry unregisters the agent
- [ ] Private volume cleanup is configurable
- [ ] Handles case where container already stopped/removed
- [ ] Unit tests for cleanup scenarios
